6: Whoa, that is SPICY! What is it?!
11:
From what I can see, a mountain of
pepper.
16:
Aw, getting this "seasoning" thing
right is hard! Isn't there a button or
an AI tool I can use?
21:
Is it... really that hard? I always
thought seasoning's a matter of
personal taste.
24:
I've never eaten anything that
wasn't synthesized before...
27:
I spent my whole life eating AdTaste
enhanced food. I guess I'll just have
to get used to the kick.
30:
You don't have to get used to it. If
you only pull back on the pepper a
bit...
33:
How are you feeling, aside from the
food? You're not seasick or anything?
36:
Nope. The balancers in my earwear
compensate for any disorientation.
39:
My cybernetic eye and aural
enhancement units keep me on a
steady keel. My nervous system's
also been upgraded, so a little boat
rocking won't faze me.
42:
You've undergone a lot of
enhancements, huh.
46:
Cybernetic add-ons come in handy.
I could stare at the sky for days
without blinking.
50:
But the nerve upgrade surgery DID
hurt, like you wouldn't believe. I was
in so much pain I must've thrown up
a hundred times. But Love was there
with me, so it was all right.
55:
Just imagining it is making me
shiver...
58:
Well, it didn't kill me and now I'm
stronger!
61:
I wouldn't be able to do my job as
Love's partner if I wasn't.
67:
How did you become a
troubleshooter, Bulleta?
71:
Asking someone about their origin
story? You need to unlock some
serious friendship levels for that.
76: Oh? I thought we were pretty close.
80:
We are. I'm just saying you can't
drop that question on someone
without a little grinding, you know?
84:
Gather 'round, kids. I'll tell you my
tale.
85:
It all started when an NPC girl
accidentally unlocked her hero job
class.
94:
Nice moves, intern! You'll have to tell
me how you learned that at the pub
after!
99:
Thank you, sir! Some chicken
nuggets would go well with that
drink, sir!
102:
Cheeky little—
Who said anything about picking up
your tab?
104:
All right, we advance. We miss any
units in this redevelopment sector
and the boss'll tear us a new one.
105:
The person with the most confirmed
kills will get whatever meal they
want.
112:
But Captain! If I recall correctly, our
mission parameters said we're
supposed to evacuate any citizenry!
115:
You've got a good memory, intern.
But you missed the fine print.
116:
"Those suspected of infection must
be terminated." Those are our orders.
118:
Besides, this here's the slums. It'd be
a miracle if the brat WASN'T infected.
121:
...So, what? You're saying every slum
dweller is going to be treated like a
rogue unit?
125:
That the circumstances surrounding
a person is what decides their fate?!
127:
That's exactly what I mean, intern.
Society can only function when
everyone is clear on their roles.
131:
That's the most heartless thing I've
ever heard. I can't follow those
orders!
137:
Sorry, everyone! I'm going to have to
ask you to step back before I wallop
you!
143:
*sigh* So much for landing a job.
Sorry, Mom and Dad...
146:
If it's a job you want, I have a
proposition for you.
149:
What do you say to being a free
agent?
155:
And that's how Love and I became
partners.
164:
Love pulled some strings and got
them into a corporation-managed
school.
167:
That should have raised some flags,
in retrospect. How many freelance
hackers can drop a huge stack of
credits to pay for a total stranger's
upkeep?
175:
I think I was so psyched about the
idea of being a hero that it slipped
my mind.
179:
At the time, I figured it was going to
be smooth sailing from there. Shows
me how much I know, huh?
180:
Love thought I was a superhero.
Thing is, she has a mind as sharp as
a laser scalpel. I've got to stay on
my toes just to keep up.
183:
I didn't want to let her down, so I
started training like mad, underwent
all kinds of enhancements, took on
life-and-death jobs... all so I could
be the hero she saw in me.
186:
I get it. Meeting Love changed you. I
can tell how close you two are.
192:
So close the dome couldn't contain
us. How's that for an epic friendship?!
200:
Oh, sorry. You didn't say anything
wrong; I was wondering if playing
the hero all the time doesn't weigh
on you.
205:
Of course it does! And I've got
enough regrets to fill this entire
ocean!
211:
Yeah. But hardships are what forge
heroes.
217:
And looking at this sunset makes all
the struggles worth it.
220:
Forget credits. There's no reward
that tops this.
224:
I'd love to stay and watch the stars
come out, but it's freezing up here!
225:
I've had enough sea spray for one
day! Time to go below deck and try
that bath thing! I've never had
anything other than a sonic shower
before!
228:
Sounds like a plan. I think we've got
some bubble solution too, if you
want to try.
233:
Now we're talking! Let's set a
course—for home!
